    <H1>USAGI Project - Linux IPv6 Development Project - </H1>
    
    <DIV id="about-us">
      <P><strong>USAGI(<font color="red">U</font>niver<font color="red">SA</font>l
	  play<font color="red">G</font>round for <font color="red">I</font>pv6)
	  Project</strong> works to deliver the production quality IPv6 
	  and IPsec(for both IPv4 and IPv6) protocol stack
	for the Linux system, tightly collaborating with
	<a href="http://www.wide.ad.jp/">WIDE Project</a>,
	<a href="http://www.kame.net/">KAME Project</a> and
	<a href="http://www.tahi.org/">TAHI Project</a>.
	USAGI Project is run by volunteers from various organizations. 
	At this moment, the volunteers are from Japan, however, we are glad to work 
	with volunteers in any country in the world. We want to contribute to the 
	Linux community and to the IPv6 community via the delivery of IPv6 protocol stack.
      </P>
    </DIV>
    
